Promote the training of Namibian students and promote the international visibility of the capacity of research in Namibia and Namibian scientists at the international level through the exploitation of observations in the field, their communication and development;

2.2.1.3

Facilitate staff exchanges and the development of teaching material and scientific disclosure on climate change in the Republic of Namibia, to encourage scientific and technical training and awareness of the general public;

2.2.1.4

Contributes through analysis and communication scientific results, to the description of the state of the atmosphere in relation to the climate in Namibia (desertification, drought, ocean warming), basis for the implementation of the Climate

Change Strategy and Action Plan (CCSAP) of the Ministry of Environment and

Tourism of the Republic of Namibia;

2.2.1.5

Enter field observations in a long-term perspective in contributing to maintaining and radiation of observations in Henties Bay, recently labelled as regional station by the World Meteorological Organization (WMO); and

2.2.1.6

Promote the conclusion of any subsequent agreement necessary for the implementation of cooperation activities envisaged by this Declaration of Intent

